WEBVTT

00:07.000 --> 00:09.033
Here you go.
Have fun and good luck.

00:09.100 --> 00:10.667
Thanks.

00:10.734 --> 00:12.767
I can't believe it.

00:16.133 --> 00:17.701
Hi.

00:17.767 --> 00:19.267
I'm Joan.

00:19.334 --> 00:20.767
Hi.

00:20.834 --> 00:23.133
Cal... are you Irish or...

00:23.200 --> 00:25.467
No, I'm English, actually.
Oh.

00:25.534 --> 00:27.467
That's so neat.

00:27.534 --> 00:30.200
So, what do you do?
I'm a furrier.

00:30.267 --> 00:32.467
Is that... like, fur coats?

00:32.534 --> 00:36.033
Fur coats, wraps,
stoles, hats,

00:36.100 --> 00:38.367
mainly fur coats, though.

00:38.434 --> 00:40.467
How about you?

00:40.534 --> 00:42.801
Um, I have to meet my friend.

00:42.868 --> 00:44.801
Well, maybe we can catch up later.

00:47.601 --> 00:49.934
Would you like one or two?

00:57.834 --> 00:59.100
Hey.

00:59.167 --> 01:00.901
Lose a bet?

01:00.968 --> 01:02.400
Basically.

01:02.467 --> 01:05.233
My friend over there dragged me along.

01:05.300 --> 01:06.934
If we were in a hotel room

01:07.000 --> 01:09.067
and you could order one
thing from room service,

01:09.133 --> 01:11.734
would it be chocolate cake,
strawberries, or warm honey?

01:13.767 --> 01:16.000
I beg your pardon?

01:16.067 --> 01:17.667
Oh.

01:17.734 --> 01:19.501
I got to take this.

01:19.567 --> 01:21.300
Yeah. what's going on?

01:21.367 --> 01:23.901
Hey. Uh, what's your ETA?
Oh, I don't know.

01:23.968 --> 01:25.567
You can't hurry love, Foster.

01:25.634 --> 01:27.968
Can I get a lager?
I hope that's your first drink.

01:28.033 --> 01:30.934
All right. D.C. police are looking
for a guy named Eric Matheson.

01:31.000 --> 01:34.100
He's been on the run for 2 days since
his wife was found beaten to death.

01:34.167 --> 01:36.267
So, they want us interviewing
friends and family

01:36.334 --> 01:38.200
To help determine if anybody's
helping him evade arrest.

01:38.267 --> 01:40.701
And I've already gotten Loker
and Torres in the field.

01:40.767 --> 01:42.901
Chardonnay, please.
I don't care...

01:42.968 --> 01:45.534
if he personally inspected
it before he shipped it.

01:45.601 --> 01:47.734
The painting's scratched,
all right?

01:47.801 --> 01:49.501
What are you talking about?
Tell him... you tell France.

01:49.567 --> 01:51.400
He's paying for the restoration.

01:51.467 --> 01:53.968
Otherwise, the whole thing
comes back his way.

01:54.033 --> 01:56.334
Collector?

01:56.400 --> 01:57.601
Dealer.

01:57.667 --> 01:59.734
I'm a curator.

01:59.801 --> 02:03.267
Really?
Really.

02:03.334 --> 02:05.267
I don't know.

02:05.334 --> 02:07.734
I guess the upside to having
been through a marriage before

02:07.801 --> 02:09.868
is that I not only know
what I'm looking for,

02:09.934 --> 02:12.434
but I know what I don't want.

02:12.501 --> 02:14.934
I just want to be happy.
Yeah, I know what you mean.

02:15.000 --> 02:17.367
Like for me, right...

02:17.434 --> 02:19.934
This one thing is very,
very, very important to me.

02:20.000 --> 02:23.634
It may seem old-fashioned
to you, but that's fidelity.

02:23.701 --> 02:25.467
Yeah. For some reason,
I feel the need

02:25.534 --> 02:26.968
to be up front about that.
Heh.

02:27.033 --> 02:29.167
That's not old-fashioned.
It's important to me, too.

02:29.234 --> 02:30.534
Uh-huh.

02:30.601 --> 02:32.367
You know, the entire time I
was married, I never cheated.

02:32.434 --> 02:35.667
I was tempted and
certainly accused of it,

02:35.734 --> 02:38.000
but I never strayed...

02:38.067 --> 02:40.834
never.
hmm.

02:40.901 --> 02:43.968
Um, so,
what are your hobbies?

02:44.033 --> 02:46.501
What do you like to do on the weekends?

02:46.567 --> 02:49.434
I run a company that shrink-wraps
poodles for international travel.

02:49.501 --> 02:51.601
Um, um,

02:51.667 --> 02:54.033
I have to, uh,
go feed my meter. Ok.

02:54.100 --> 02:56.133
Um, I'll be right back.
Could you hold that thought?

02:56.200 --> 02:58.200
Yeah. I'll, uh,
save your seat.

02:58.267 --> 03:00.334
Thanks.

03:03.100 --> 03:04.834
Hey.
Hey.

03:04.901 --> 03:08.434
So, uh,
in answer to your question from earlier,

03:08.501 --> 03:11.133
it's warm honey, right?
Heh heh heh.

03:11.200 --> 03:14.133
You should call me sometime.

03:14.200 --> 03:15.634
Ok.

03:17.000 --> 03:23.074
